reviews.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice Upgrade
reviews.author: Wryter
reviews.content: Just received mine. I had a series 6, but decided it was time to upgrade. Because I had a previous watch set up on my iPhone SE (Gen 2), the transfer of all the settings took less than five minutes. My old band transferred easily. I wear my watch on my left wrist but I have it set up to wear as a left handed person (like I was going to wear it on my right wrist). That way the Digital Crown is on the lower-left of my wrist. The way it was before caused me to activate the Digital Crown accidentally. When the transfer was made to the new watch, it transferred that setting also. A couple of important things to note: first, it doesn’t come with an advanced energy charger plug-in. Just the C cable, so if you are using a regular Apple plug-in, you’re not going to see the speed charging. Secondly, a note said I needed iOS 18 on my phone to set the watch up automatically. So upgrade your phone before you attempt to transfer to your new watch. Otherwise, you’ll need to set it up manually. Just the 2 mm difference in size between the old and new watches seems like it is a lot more. Great display, seems brighter. I look forward to playing with the apps, particularly the sleep apnea one, since I have been diagnosed with sleep apnea but can’t sleep with a CPAP full face mask on. I also look forward to seeing what the new fitness app is like. If it hadn’t been for a few new features, though, I probably wouldn’t have upgraded. It’s basically the same watch with a few added features.
reviews.timestamp: Reviewed in the United States September 25, 2024
